and after you've done your work
with the stories, review your phrases.

251
00:11:53.330 --> 00:11:55.352
Reviewing phrases is really quick, right?

252
00:11:55.552 --> 00:11:56.980
Zoom zoom and you're ready to go!

253
00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:58.440
But it's important that you
review your phrases

254
00:11:58.470 --> 00:12:01.300
in the RAIO app
every single day, okay?

255
00:12:01.330 --> 00:12:04.060
Not just once every week,
every single day.

256
00:12:04.080 --> 00:12:05.420
Keep that streak up.

257
00:12:05.450 --> 00:12:08.460
Don't lose that streak.
Every single day!

258
00:12:08.490 --> 00:12:10.860
And that's gonna help you internalize

259
00:12:10.890 --> 00:12:14.940
the vocabulary and the grammar a lot,
a lot faster, a lot faster.

260
00:12:14.970 --> 00:12:16.860
So if you don't use RAIO app,

261
00:12:16.890 --> 00:12:20.340
it's going to take a lot longer
to be fluent.

262
00:12:20.360 --> 00:12:20.580
Okay?

263
00:12:20.610 --> 00:12:23.460
So you wanna make sure
that you do all of these things.

264
00:12:23.480 --> 00:12:24.620
Listen to the normal version,

265
00:12:24.650 --> 00:12:28.500
the interactive version, and review
your phrases in the app every day.

266
00:12:28.520 --> 00:12:30.060
And remember,
you can download the audios

267
00:12:30.080 --> 00:12:33.300
and the transcript if you need
to practice outside the course, right?

268
00:12:33.320 --> 00:12:34.180
You have the button here.

269
00:12:34.210 --> 00:12:37.620
"Download transcript + audio file"
if you're going on an airplane

270
00:12:37.650 --> 00:12:40.940
or something like that,
where you need the files downloaded.

271
00:12:40.960 --> 00:12:41.481
Okay?

272
00:12:41.681 --> 00:12:45.340
Now, remember RAIO rule number three.

273
00:12:45.360 --> 00:12:46.560
Well, we haven't gone through all

274
00:12:46.580 --> 00:12:50.660
the rules yet, but we will very shortly
in the next section here or not the next

275
00:12:50.680 --> 00:12:53.420
section but a little bit further
down here in chapter one.

276
00:12:53.450 --> 00:12:56.940
RAIO rule number three,
"don't take notes."

277
00:12:56.970 --> 00:12:58.620
Do not take notes.

278
00:12:58.650 --> 00:12:59.660
Okay?

279
00:12:59.690 --> 00:13:02.740
This is modern learning, right?

280
00:13:02.770 --> 00:13:04.300
You don't need to take notes.

281
00:13:04.330 --> 00:13:07.140
Notes is a very,
very inefficient way of learning.

282
00:13:07.170 --> 00:13:09.100
Let the RAIO app do the work for you.

283
00:13:09.130 --> 00:13:13.320
Let spaced repetition,
let the algorithm do the work for you.

284
00:13:13.350 --> 00:13:15.060
I know it's a new way of learning.

285
00:13:15.080 --> 00:13:18.340
I know some of you guys will say
"no, but Kale, I love taking notes."

286
00:13:18.370 --> 00:13:20.740
"I love writing down everything."

287
00:13:20.770 --> 00:13:22.180
Please trust me.

288
00:13:22.210 --> 00:13:24.140
Don't.
Don't waste your time doing it.

289
00:13:24.170 --> 00:13:28.380
I know you might feel like you're learning
a little bit by doing it,

290
00:13:28.410 --> 00:13:34.140
but that time you spend taking notes,
you could spend that time consuming

291
00:13:34.170 --> 00:13:38.420
stories and reviewing phrases,
and that's going to be way more beneficial

292
00:13:38.450 --> 00:13:41.220
to your English than
writing down notes, right?

293
00:13:41.240 --> 00:13:44.100
And typically, we don't look
at the notes anyways afterwards.

294
00:13:44.130 --> 00:13:46.907
Typically.
But even if you do, try.

295
00:13:47.107 --> 00:13:47.780
Please try.

296
00:13:47.810 --> 00:13:49.380
Don't take notes.

297
00:13:49.410 --> 00:13:53.860
Let the method do it's job, right?

298
00:13:53.890 --> 00:13:56.844
Watch the stories,
do the exercise listening to the stories,

299
00:13:57.044 --> 00:13:59.100
and review your phrases at the end of this

300
00:13:59.130 --> 00:14:01.620
section and then go back
and come back tomorrow.

301
00:14:01.650 --> 00:14:03.100
All right?
Awesome.

302
00:14:03.130 --> 00:14:06.460
Now remember, you may
go to the next section,

303
00:14:06.490 --> 00:14:07.860
the next story,

304
00:14:07.880 --> 00:14:11.580
only when you're able to answer all
the questions in the interactive version

305
00:14:11.610 --> 00:14:16.660
correctly, out loud, on time,
with your eyes closed, right?

306
00:14:16.690 --> 00:14:19.200
Okay, awesome.
And remember, input creates output.

307
00:14:19.200 --> 00:14:20.820
That's RAIO
rule number five.

308
00:14:20.850 --> 00:14:22.460
So be patient here.

309
00:14:22.490 --> 00:14:25.900
Remember, your speaking ability will come!

310
00:14:25.920 --> 00:14:27.600
First you will improve your listening,

311
00:14:27.800 --> 00:14:29.500
and then your speaking comes
automatically.

312
00:14:29.530 --> 00:14:32.700
You do not necessarily need
to speak to improve your speaking.

313
00:14:32.730 --> 00:14:35.580
That's just how language learning works.

314
00:14:35.610 --> 00:14:38.000
By speaking a lot,
you improve your confidence.

315
00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:41.500
You get rid of some fears and anxieties
and mental blocks and things like that.

316
00:14:41.530 --> 00:14:43.900
That's why we have
the RAIO Conversation Club.

317
00:14:43.930 --> 00:14:46.539
But to really make a big improvement

318
00:14:46.739 --> 00:14:47.910
in your speaking,

319
00:14:48.110 --> 00:14:49.220
you need to listen.

320
00:14:49.250 --> 00:14:50.380
You need to consume.

321
00:14:50.410 --> 00:14:52.340
Input creates output, right?

322
00:14:52.360 --> 00:14:55.800
So right now, what you're doing is when
you're listening to the stories and when

323
00:14:55.830 --> 00:15:00.340
you're reviewing your phrases in the RAIO
app, you're both listening and reading.

324
00:15:00.370 --> 00:15:03.660
So you're improving all these
four things at the same time.

325
00:15:03.680 --> 00:15:06.580
You're also improving your pronunciation,
even though you don't know it.

326
00:15:06.610 --> 00:15:10.700
But the more you consume the language,
the more you become aware

327
00:15:10.720 --> 00:15:14.520
of pronunciation and the better
your pronunciation will be.

328
00:15:14.550 --> 00:15:19.660
We do have pronunciation classes further
down in the course.

329
00:15:19.690 --> 00:15:21.540
But for now, keep that in mind,

330
00:15:21.570 --> 00:15:22.700
input creates output!

